<refentry id="fn_lcase">
  <refmeta>
    <refentrytitle>lcase</refentrytitle>
    <refmiscinfo>string</refmiscinfo>
  </refmeta>
  <refnamediv>
    <refname>lcase</refname>
    <refpurpose>Converts string argument to lower case</refpurpose>
  </refnamediv>
  <refsynopsisdiv>
    <funcsynopsis id="fsyn_lcase">
      <funcprototype id="fproto_lcase">
        <funcdef><function>lcase</function></funcdef>
        <paramdef><parameter>str</parameter> string</paramdef>
      </funcprototype>
    </funcsynopsis>
  </refsynopsisdiv>
  <refsect1 id="desc_lcase"><title>Description</title>
    <para>lcase returns a copy of string str with all the uppercase alphabetical
    characters converted to corresponding lowercase letters. This includes
    also the diacritic letters present in the ISO 8859/1 standard in range
    192 - 222 decimal, excluding the character 223, German double-s which
    stays the same.</para>
    <para>lower is an alias for lcase.</para>
    <screen>lcase('AbracadabrA')  -&gt; 'abracadabra'</screen>
  </refsect1>
</refentry>
